[Predictions]

@Jonjon No disrespect, but imo your appraisal of Taira's striking feels very faith-based and speculative. Yes, Taira is a good striker. We saw that in the Perez fight, plus what he did to Park and Hernandez. But the only one of those guys who is arguably elite is Perez. I don't doubt that Taira has leveled up his striking since the Royval fight. He showed that by nearly KO'ing Park with that straight right (iirc). But in the Moreno fight most recently, he seemed uninterested in the stand-up except as a means to set up takedowns. He landed a good uppercut in the second round and that was about it. His game plan was 100% get to the ground, not feint takedowns and land something on the feet. And Moreno found the mark on Taira a couple of times, just not with any power at all. Maybe Taira bullies Van, but if he does, it's going to be on the ground, not the feet. Again, I'm sure Taira has improved since two fights ago, and MMA Math is what it is, but it means something that he nearly got TKO'd in R3 by Royval, and Royval nearly got TKO'd in R3 by Van.

